This paper discusses the position bias in recommender systems, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR) and human-computer interaction (HC) research. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.HC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also focuses on digital libraries (DL) and their recommendation systems, which suggests cs.DL as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the study involves analyzing user behavior and click-through rates, which could fall under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and computers and society (cs.CY).
